#. <section class="sutta" id="sn45.160"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn45.160:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 45"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 45"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.160:0.2"
msgid "12. Balakaraṇīyavagga"
msgstr "12. Hard Work"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn45.160:0.3"
msgid "160. Nadīsutta"
msgstr "160. A River"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.54"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.160:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gaṅgā nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose that, although the Ganges river slants, slopes, and "
"inclines to the east,"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.2"
msgid "Atha mahājanakāyo āgaccheyya kuddālapiṭakaṃ ādāya:"
msgstr "a large crowd were to come along with a spade and basket, saying:"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.3"
msgid ""
"‘mayaṃ imaṃ gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ pacchāninnaṃ karissāma pacchāpoṇaṃ "
"pacchāpabbhāran’ti."
msgstr "‘We’ll make this Ganges river slant, slope, and incline to the west!’"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.5"
msgid ""
"api nu so mahājanakāyo gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ pacchāninnaṃ kareyya pacchāpoṇaṃ "
"pacchāpabbhāran”ti?"
msgstr "Would they succeed?”"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir."

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.7"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.8"
msgid "“Gaṅgā, bhante, nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā."
msgstr "The Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east."

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.9"
msgid "Sā na sukarā pacchāninnaṃ kātuṃ pacchāpoṇaṃ pacchāpabbhāraṃ."
msgstr "It’s not easy to make it slant, slope, and incline to the west."

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.10"
msgid "Yāvadeva pana so mahājanakāyo kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti."
msgstr "That large crowd will eventually get weary and frustrated.”"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.11"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāventaṃ ariyaṃ "
"aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarontaṃ rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā mittā vā amaccā "
"vā ñātī vā ñātisālohitā vā bhogehi abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyyuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, while a mendicant develops and cultivates the noble "
"eightfold path, if rulers or their ministers, friends or colleagues, "
"relatives or family should invite them to accept wealth, saying:"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.12"
msgid ""
"‘ehambho purisa, kiṃ te ime kāsāvā anudahanti, kiṃ muṇḍo "
"kapālamanusaṃcarasi. Ehi, hīnāyāvattitvā bhoge ca bhuñjassu, puññāni ca "
"karohī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Please, mister, why let these ocher robes torment you? Why follow the "
"practice of shaving your head and carrying an alms bowl? Come, return to a "
"lesser life, enjoy wealth, and make merit!’"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.13"
msgid ""
"So vata, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvento ariyaṃ "
"aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaronto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissatīti—"
"netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply impossible for a mendicant who develops and cultivates the noble "
"eightfold path to reject the training and return to a lesser life."

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.14"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.15"
msgid ""
"Yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ dīgharattaṃ vivekaninnaṃ vivekapoṇaṃ "
"vivekapabbhāraṃ taṃ vata hīnāyāvattissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"Because for a long time that mendicant’s mind has slanted, sloped, and "
"inclined to seclusion. So it’s impossible for them to return to a lesser "
"life."

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.16"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti ariyaṃ "
"aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant develop the noble eightfold path?"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.17"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ … pe … "
"sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ "
"vossaggapariṇāmiṃ …"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, "
"right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right "
"immersion, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as "
"letting go."

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.18"
msgid ""
"evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti, ariyaṃ "
"aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant develops and cultivates the noble eightfold path.”"

msgctxt "sn45.160:1.19"
msgid "(Yadapi balakaraṇīyaṃ, tadapi vitthāretabbaṃ.)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn45.160:1.20"
msgid "Dvādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn45.160:1.21"
msgid "Balakaraṇīyavaggo chaṭṭho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.160:2.1"
msgid "Balaṃ bījañca nāgo ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.160:2.2"
msgid "rukkho kumbhena sūkiyā;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.160:2.3"
msgid "Ākāsena ca dve meghā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.160:2.4"
msgid "nāvā āgantukā nadīti."
msgstr ""
